mers%20that%20automatically%20fixes%20coding%20mistakes%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20Young%20Geniuses%20series%20spotlights%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20founders%2C%20innovators%2C%20and%20thinkers%20who%20are%20trying%20to%20reshape%20industries%20and%20solve%20global%20challenges.%20See%20more%20stories%20from%20the%20series%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-geniuses-child-prodigies-inventing-founding-science-business-tech-solutions%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20reach%20out%20to%20editor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fpeter-gelling%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPeter%20Gelling%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20share%20your%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3EI%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20machine%20learning%2C%20how%20we%20could%20have%20code%20fix%20itself%2C%20and%20how%20to%20automate%20an%20entire%20process.%20It%20took%20me%20almost%20a%20year%2C%20but%20I%20got%20it%20to%20work%20in%20a%20prototype.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20start%20of%20my%20company%20that%20I'm%20now%20running%20full-time%20at%2022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2240d07729-fed0-4663-b22c-87cd9078a4c8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBy%20my%20senior%20year%2C%20I%20took%20my%20first%20VC%20call%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20VC%20reached%20out%20to%20me%20and%20said%20they%20were%20interested%20in%20what%20I%20was%20building%2C%20but%20there%20was%20no%20monetization%2C%20so%20I%20realized%20I%20should%20focus%20on%20something%20even%20bigger%2C%20which%20turned%20into%20my%20company%2C%20Kodezi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20start%20an%20AI%20company%20at%2017%2C%20the%20biggest%20step%20I%20took%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-cold-email-clients-exact-template-freelancers-business-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewriting%20emails%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20realized%20you%20can%20email%20anyone%20by%20Googling%20their%20email%20address.%20I%20emailed%20CEOs%2C%20startup%20founders%2C%20AI%20researchers%2C%20and%20venture%20capitalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20reached%20out%20to%20try%20to%20get%20internships%20and%20learn%20from%20people%20who%20were%20further%20ahead%20than%20me.%20Over%20time%2C%20those%20emails%20evolved%20into%20conversations%20about%20what%20I%20was%20building%20with%20some%20really%20big%20names.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20found%20an%20event%20called%20Orlando%20Synapse%2C%20and%20I%20emailed%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20a%20senior%20in%20high%20school%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20have%20%24500%20for%20a%20booth.%20Is%20there%20any%20way%20I%20can%20come%20for%20free%3F%20This%20is%20what%20I'm%20building.%26quot%3B%20Someone%20replied%20within%20a%20few%20hours%20and%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BSure%2C%20here's%20the%20free%20booth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cdb3a9db-bf8a-4beb-ac74-995f36a8c894%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20posted%20on%20LinkedIn%20that%20I%20attended%20the%20event%20and%20got%20one%20of%20my%20first%20angel%20investors%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20received%20a%20%2420%2C000%20investment%20before%20I%20turned%2018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20biggest%20challenge%20was%20getting%20others%20to%20say%20yes%20from%20an%20investment%20standpoint%2C%20because%20back%20then%2C%20there%20was%20no%20ChatGPT%2C%20and%20AI's%20use%20cases%20were%20still%20seen%20as%20experimental.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20difficult%20to%20convince%20investors%20to%20back%20an%20AI-first%20code%20platform%20coming%20from%20a%20teenager.%20There%20was%20skepticism%20not%20just%20about%20the%20technology%2C%20but%20about%20whether%20I%20could%20execute%20at%20that%20level.%20Once%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsc%2Fhow-generative-ai-is-transforming-production-for-brands-and-creators%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egenerative%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20became%20widely%20adopted%2C%20the%20narrative%20around%20what%20we%20were%20building%20became%20much%20easier%20to%20understand.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224f87047b-2a7e-43ae-96c0-79da026a86e4%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20raised%20%24800%2C000%20before%20I%20turned%2019%20and%20%242%20million%20before%20I%20turned%2022%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20my%20strategies%20to%20achieve%20this%20was%20learning%20how%20to%20answer%20three%20questions%20from%20investors%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3EWhat%20are%20you%20building%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhy%20does%20this%20matter%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhy%20will%20this%20be%20a%20billion-dollar%20company%3F%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20needed%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20to%20convince%20them%20that%20I%20was%20the%20right%20person%20to%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20overcame%20investor%20rejections%20by%20framing%20the%20calls%20as%20me%20interviewing%20them%2C%20rather%20than%20me%20being%20interviewed.%20I%20started%20trying%20to%20understand%20who%20they%20are%2C%20why%20they%20invest%20in%20these%20companies%2C%20and%20what%20their%20goal%20is.%20This%20helped%20me%20decide%20whether%20they%20were%20the%20right%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cd704532-b2c9-467f-8e4d-1879746e20a1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnother%20challenge%20was%20deciding%20whether%20to%20go%20to%20college%20or%20work%20full-time%20at%20my%20company%20at%2017%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20applied%20to%2060%20colleges%2C%20got%20into%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%2C%20including%20Ivy%20League%20schools%2C%20and%20ultimately%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fskipped-college-made-600000-online-business-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eskip%20college%20completely%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20really%20want%20to%20go%20to%20college%26quot%3B%20was%20still%20the%20answer%20I'd%20give%20people%2C%20and%20when%20investors%20asked%2C%20I'd%20say%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20really%20know%2C%20maybe%E2%80%A6%26quot%3B%20My%20uncertainty%20about%20it%20was%20one%20reason%20some%20investors%20were%20uncertain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20realized%20I'd%20probably%20hate%20myself%20if%20I%20did%20go%20to%20college%2C%20because%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20the%20same%20opportunities%2C%20and%20I%20could%20always%20go%20to%20college%20later.%20If%20I%20wanted%20to%20build%20an%20AI%20company%20after%20I%20graduated%2C%20thousands%20of%20others%20would've%20already%20done%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f8385945-0f0c-4801-8d42-66647b772f57%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20lot%20of%20my%20friends%20would%20be%20graduating%20from%20college%20and%20then%20would%20find%20jobs%2C%20but%20this%20was%20me%20finding%20my%20job%20now%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20have%20regrets%20about%20skipping%20college.%20I%20do%20think%20college%20provides%20a%20built-in%20social%20environment%20that's%20hard%20to%20replicate.%20It's%20easier%20to%20make%20friends%20when%20you're%20surrounded%20by%20peers%20in%20the%20same%20life%20stage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20the%20people%20I%20spend%20time%20with%20now%20are%20builders%20%E2%80%94%20young%20founders%2C%20owners%2C%20operators%2C%20and%20ambitious%20executives%20who%20are%20obsessed%20with%20creating%20something%20meaningful.%20That%20shared%20mindset%20is%20powerful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20always%20an%20opportunity%20cost%2C%20and%20for%20me%2C%20that%20trade-off%20was%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22726e6b62-1f01-475c-81fb-9a0dbdb436f6%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EFor%20other%20aspiring%20AI%20company%20founders%2C%20I%20recommend%20doing%20whatever%20you're%20doing%20as%20quickly%20as%20you%20can%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWithout%20feedback%20from%20people%20who%20aren't%20your%20friends%2C%20you%20won't%20truly%20know%20whether%20what%20you're%20building%20connects%20with%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20don't%20strive%20for%20a%20metric%20like%20%26quot%3Bsuccess%26quot%3B%20that%20will%20limit%20you.%20Rather%20than%20chasing%20external%20success%2C%20chase%20internal%20excellence%2C%20because%20that%20will%20lead%20to%20a%20successful%20outcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22fbfaa014-1417-4f95-b8c2-bcf6cceb78f1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20I'm%2030%2C%20I%20see%20myself%20still%20building%20my%20company%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20the%20world%20needs%20more%20innovation%2C%20and%20that's%20where%20younger%20founders%20will%20come%20into%20play%2C%20specifically%20with%20the%20rise%20of%20AI%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20now%20been%20running%20the%20company%20for%20six%20years.%20We've%20grown%20to%20over%2035%20employees.%20My%20next%20goal%20is%20to%20dominate%20the%20code%20maintenance%20layer%20for%20enterprise%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20want%20Kodezi%20to%20become%20the%20default%20system%20companies%20rely%20on%20to%20keep%20their%20codebases%20healthy%20over%20time.%20If%20writing%20code%20is%20like%20building%20a%20car%2C%20then%20maintaining%20it%20requires%20a%20mechanic.%20Our%20mission%20is%20to%20become%20the%20automated%20mechanic%20for%20software.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-22-year-old-skipped-college-build-ai-company-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772100301000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f612ae8408f6671804515%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-22-year-old-skipped-college-build-ai-company-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20young%20founder%20from%20Bangladesh%20shares%20his%20journey%20to%20creating%20his%20AI%20company%2C%20Kodezi%2C%20while%20balancing%20finishing%20high%20school%20and%20entrepreneurship.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Robin%20Madell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-22-year-old-skipped-college-build-ai-company-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%224Chan%20knew%20about%20Jeffrey%20Epstein's%20death%2038%20minutes%20before%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%20The%20FBI%20tried%20to%20figure%20out%20how.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221608%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jeffrey%20Epstein%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699c5ea72237a6a8f0cda1aa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221162%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJeffrey%20Epstein%3Cp%3EDOJ's%20Epstein%20files%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%204Chan%20user%20posted%20about%20Jeffrey%20Epstein's%20death%20before%20anyone%20else.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Epstein%20Files%20show%20how%20the%20FBI%20tried%20to%20identify%20who%20the%20person%20was.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEpstein%20and%20Christopher%20Poole%2C%20the%20reclusive%204Chan%20founder%2C%20discussed%20meeting%20in%202011.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20many%20mysteries%20surrounding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeffrey-epstein-planned-inheritance-marriage-karyna-shuliak-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJeffrey%20Epstein%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20how%2C%20exactly%2C%20a%20website%20famous%20for%20pornography%20and%20white%20nationalism%20got%20the%20scoop%20on%20his%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%208%3A16%20a.m.%20on%20August%2010%2C%202019%2C%20an%20anonymous%204Chan%20user%20posted%2C%20%26quot%3Bdon't%20ask%20me%20how%20I%20know%2C%20but%20Epstein%20died%20an%20hour%20ago%20from%20hanging%2C%20cardiac%20arrest.%20Screencap%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20first%20public%20indication%20that%20Epstein%2C%20awaiting%20trial%20for%20sex-trafficking%20charges%20in%20Manhattan's%20Metropolitan%20Correctional%20Center%2C%20died%20while%20in%20the%20custody%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.buzzfeednews.com%2Farticle%2Fjanelytvynenko%2Ffdny-review-jeffrey-epstein-4chan-post%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBuzzFeed%20News%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20beat%20ABC%20News%20journalist%20Aaron%20Katersky's%20post%20about%20Epstein's%20death%20on%20Twitter%2C%20now%20known%20as%20X%2C%20by%2038%20minutes.%20A%20few%20minutes%20later%2C%20the%20ABC%20News%20website%20published%20the%20first%20article%20about%20Epstein's%20apparent%20suicide%20in%20jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20newly%20released%20Epstein%20files%20show%20that%20the%20Justice%20Department%20tried%20to%20identify%20the%204Chan%20user%20behind%20the%20posts%20%E2%80%94%20but%20couldn't%20figure%20it%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20documents%20show%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepstein-files-consequences-resignations-brad-karp-kathy-ruemmler-wasserman%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20Justice%20Department%3C%2Fa%3E%20subpoenaed%204Chan%20for%20the%20user's%20IP%20addresses%20four%20days%20after%20the%20posts%20were%20made%20as%20part%20of%20the%20FBI's%20investigation%20into%20Epstein's%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20there%2C%20the%20trail%20went%20cold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20anonymous%20user%20made%20a%20total%20of%20four%20posts%2C%20according%20to%204Chan's%20response%20to%20the%20subpoena.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFielding%20questions%20from%20other%20users%2C%20they%20gave%20responses%20that%20appeared%20fluent%20in%20medical%20jargon%2C%20screenshots%20of%20the%20posts%20show.%20They%20said%20his%20body%20was%20intubated%2C%20had%20fluid%20infused%2C%20and%20was%20moved%20to%20an%20emergency%20room%20in%20lower%20Manhattan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20user%20also%20provided%20some%20of%20the%20earliest%20unproven%20conspiracy%20theories%20about%20Epstein's%20death.%20In%20one%20post%2C%20which%20was%20later%20deleted%20but%20provided%20to%20the%20FBI%20in%20response%20to%20the%20subpoena%2C%20the%20user%20said%20someone%20may%20have%20swapped%20out%20Epstein's%20body%20because%20of%20a%20mysterious%20van%20seen%20the%20previous%20night%2C%20DOJ%20records%20show.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20guys%20i%20am%20shaking%20right%20now%20but%20i%20think%20they%20switched%20him%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20anonymous%20poster%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeffrey-epstein-files-reveal-islands-renovation-designs-photos-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erecords%20made%20public%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Justice%20Department%20include%20multiple%20photos%20of%20Epstein's%20corpse.%20His%20body%20was%20identified%20by%20a%20forensic%20pathologist%20hired%20by%20his%20brother%2C%20Mark%20Epstein%2C%20who%20later%20interred%20it%20in%20a%20cemetery%20near%20their%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20the%20IP%20addresses%204Chan%20provided%2C%20prosecutors%20subpoenaed%20AT%26amp%3BT%20for%20information%20that%20could%20identify%20people%20who%20used%20them%20at%20the%20time%20the%20posts%20were%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20told%20them%20it%20didn't%20have%20the%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAT%26amp%3BT%20is%20unable%20to%20provide%20any%20information%20in%20response%20to%20the%20Legal%20Demand%20because%20AT%26amp%3BT%20does%20not%20maintain%20records%20in%20the%20normal%20course%20of%20business%20that%20associate%20individual%20accounts%20or%20devices%20with%20wireless%20dynamic%20IP%20addresses%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20company%20employee%20said%20in%20a%20response%20to%20the%20subpoena%20included%20in%20the%20files.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Justice%20Department%20also%20subpoenaed%20T-Mobile%20for%20records%20related%20to%20the%20IP%20addresses.%20T-Mobile's%20response%20isn't%20included%20in%20the%20files.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20year%2C%20federal%20prosecutors%20in%20Manhattan%20confirmed%20they%20never%20identified%20the%204Chan%20user.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20issue%20arose%20in%20the%20discovery%20process%20for%20the%20criminal%20case%20against%20Tova%20Noel%20and%20Michael%20Thomas%2C%20the%20two%20jail%20guards%20who%20were%20supposed%20to%20be%20keeping%20an%20eye%20on%20Epstein%20the%20night%20he%20died.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Findictment-against-epstein-guards-says-napped-night-of-his-death-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EProsecutors%20had%20accused%3C%2Fa%3E%20Noel%20and%20Thomas%20of%20falsifying%20records%20related%20to%20their%20duties%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprosecutors-drop-case-against-jeffrey-epstein-jail-guards-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echarges%20that%20were%20later%20dropped%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20letter%20now%20made%20public%20in%20the%20files%2C%20prosecutors%20told%20Noel's%20attorney%2C%20Jason%20Foy%2C%20that%20they%20didn't%20know%20the%20author's%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Government%20has%20produced%20all%20records%20we%20have%20obtained%20regarding%20the%204Chan%20post%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThe%20poster%20used%20a%20dynamic%20IP%2C%20and%20therefore%20the%20records%20obtained%20did%20not%20disclose%20the%20author%20of%20the%20post.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20128-page%20Justice%20Department%20inspector%20general%20report%20on%20the%20circumstances%20surrounding%20Epstein's%20death%20detailed%20widespread%20dysfunction%20at%20the%20Metropolitan%20Correctional%20Center.%20It%20addressed%20some%20lingering%20questions%20%E2%80%94%20including%20the%20lack%20of%20functioning%20cameras%20on%20his%20cell%20tier%20and%20the%20decision%20to%20leave%20him%20without%20a%20cellmate%2C%20allowing%20him%20to%20kill%20himself%20unobserved%20%E2%80%94%20but%20made%20no%20mention%20of%20the%204chan%20posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEpstein%20appeared%20to%20be%20a%204Chan%20user%20himself%2C%20sometimes%20sending%20links%20of%204Chan%20posts%20to%20other%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Justice%20Department's%20files%20also%20show%20Epstein%20was%20acquainted%20with%20Christopher%20Poole%2C%20the%20reclusive%20founder%20of%204Chan.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2Ftech%2F879132%2Fmoot-4chan-jeffrey-epstein-meeting-pol%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPoole%20told%20The%20Verge%20that%20he%20and%20Epstein%20met%20once%20for%20lunch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20that%20he%20regrets%20%26quot%3Bhaving%20ever%20encountered%20him%20at%20all%2C%20and%20have%20deep%20sympathy%20for%20all%20of%20his%20victims.%26quot%3B%20He%20didn't%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20requests%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20DOJ's%20files%20show%20Epstein%20discussed%20having%20met%20with%20Poole%20%E2%80%94%20who%20is%20also%20known%20by%20his%204Chan%20username%2C%20moot%20%E2%80%94%20following%20an%20introduction%20by%20Boris%20Nikolic%2C%20a%20former%20science%20advisor%20to%20Bill%20Gates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3Bi%20liked%20mmot%20slot%2C%26quot%3B%20Epstein%20told%20Nikolic%20in%20a%20typo-filled%20October%202011%20email.%20%26quot%3Bi%20drove%20him%20home%2C%20he%20is%20very%20bright.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepstein-files-show-fbi-probed-4chan-posts-prison-death-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772100061000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699c5ece156648bc16a8b0c8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepstein-files-show-fbi-probed-4chan-posts-prison-death-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Epstein%20files%20address%20a%20long-running%20side%20plot%20of%20Jeffrey%20Epstein's%202019%20death%20while%20in%20jail%20on%20sex-trafficking%20charges.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jshamsian%40businessinsider.com%20(Jacob%20Shamsian)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepstein-files-show-fbi-probed-4chan-posts-prison-death-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22AI%20rewrites%20the%20economics%20of%20Amazon's%20cloud-consulting%20business%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225707%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22AWS%20CEO%20Matt%20Garman%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f388ee8408f6671803f59%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223805%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAWS%20CEO%20Matt%20Garman%3Cp%3ENoah%20Berger%2FGetty%20Images%20for%20Amazon%20Web%20Services%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAI%20is%20pushing%20radical%20changes%20on%20the%20consulting%20industry.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EClients%20of%20Amazon's%20big%20ProServe%20cloud-consulting%20group%20seek%20AI-driven%20discounts.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EProServe%20is%20embracing%20AI%20agents%20and%20aims%20to%20make%2075%25%20of%20projects%20fixed-price%2C%20documents%20show.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EClients%20are%20starting%20to%20press%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-top-management-consulting-firms-list-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Econsulting%3C%2Fa%3E%20firms%20with%20an%20awkward%20question%3A%20If%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fanthropic-ai-software-claude-microsoft-powerpoint-excel-slack-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20doing%20more%20of%20the%20work%2C%20why%20are%20we%20still%20paying%20the%20same%20fees%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20issue%20hitting%20home%20inside%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-engineers-grate-against-internal-limits-claude-code-kiro-ai-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAmazon%3C%2Fa%3E's%20cloud%20business%2C%20through%20a%20consulting%20arm%20called%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-proserve-culture-investigation-workplace-gender-discrimination-lawsuit-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EProServe%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20influences%20more%20than%20%2410%20billion%20in%20annual%20revenue%20for%20the%20tech%20giant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMajor%20customers%2C%20including%20Booking.com%20and%20Danske%20Bank%2C%20have%20%26quot%3Bproactively%26quot%3B%20sought%20to%20renegotiate%20ProServe%20contracts%2C%20pushing%20for%20what%20an%20internal%20Amazon%20document%20described%20as%20%26quot%3BAI-delivered%20pricing%2C%26quot%3B%20along%20with%20faster%20results%20at%20lower%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20GenAI%20enhances%20or%20speeds%20things%20up%2C%20they%20should%20get%20more%20value%20faster%20and%20shouldn't%20pay%20the%20same%20rates%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20document%20from%20June%20stated%2C%20summarizing%20the%20prevailing%20sentiment%20among%20ProServe%20clients.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20pressure%20is%20reshaping%20the%20ProServe%20unit.%20Internal%20documents%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider%20show%20Amazon%20reorganizing%20the%20cloud%20consulting%20arm%20around%20AI%20agents%20it%20describes%20as%20%26quot%3Bdigital%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20while%20pivoting%20away%20from%20a%20traditional%20billable-hour%20model.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20changes%20reflect%20a%20broader%20reckoning%20rippling%20through%20the%20consulting%20industry.%20The%20twin%20forces%20of%20pricing%20pressure%20and%20automation%20are%20pushing%20other%20consulting%20firms%20in%20a%20similar%20direction%2C%20accelerating%20a%20shift%20toward%20outcome-based%20pricing%20that%20charges%20for%20results%20rather%20than%20time-based%20human%20labor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20customers'%20buying%20patterns%20shifted%20to%20favor%20agile%2C%20outcome-based%2C%20Al-powered%20engagements%20with%20faster%20time%20to%20value%20and%20clear%20ROI%2C%20creating%20a%20significant%20revenue%20and%20workload%20concentration%20risk%20in%20our%20top%20revenue%20cohort%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20ProServe%20document%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22446eec24-5dca-4a9b-80fe-4179d76bfca2%5C%22%3EAI%20is%20challenging%20the%20billable-hour%20model%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EConsulting%20has%20long%20operated%20on%20a%20straightforward%20equation%3A%20revenue%20scales%20with%20headcount%20and%20hours%20worked.%20Projects%20are%20often%20priced%20on%20an%20hourly%20basis%2C%20with%20teams%20of%20engineers%2C%20architects%2C%20and%20project%20managers%20assigned%20to%20client%20engagements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20generative%20AI%20tools%20are%20now%20accelerating%20coding%2C%20documentation%2C%20and%20software%20modernization%20work.%20Tasks%20that%20once%20required%20teams%20of%20consultants%20can%20increasingly%20be%20automated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20work%20gets%20done%20faster%2C%20with%20fewer%20people%2C%20clients%20expect%20savings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProServe%20planning%20documents%20from%20June%20and%20November%20acknowledged%20that%20dynamic%2C%20noting%20customer%20demands%20for%20AI-enabled%20efficiencies%20and%20lower%20effective%20pricing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20June%20document%20outlined%20a%20%26quot%3Bfundamental%26quot%3B%20strategic%20shift%20from%20%26quot%3Btraditional%20project-based%20consulting%20to%20product-led%2C%20outcome-based%20delivery.%26quot%3B%20By%20this%20year%2C%20ProServe%20aimed%20to%20have%20up%20to%2075%25%20of%20projects%20structured%20as%20%26quot%3Bfixed-price%26quot%3B%20deals%2C%20this%20document%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAWS%20is%20not%20alone%20in%20confronting%20this%20shift.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMajor%20consulting%20firms%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faccenture-anthrophic-open-ai-deal-claude-consulting-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAccenture%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeloitte-gives-us-employees-new-job-titles-leader-role-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EDeloitte%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20made%20large-scale%20AI%20investments%20and%20increasingly%20emphasize%20outcome-based%20pricing%20in%20client%20engagements.%20Executives%20across%20the%20industry%20have%20signaled%20that%20generative%20AI%20will%20compress%20traditional%20labor-based%20work%20while%20forcing%20firms%20to%20compete%20more%20on%20measurable%20results.%20Auditing%20giant%20KPMG%2C%20for%20example%2C%20pressed%20its%20own%20auditor%20for%20lower%20fees%2C%20citing%20AI%20efficiency%20gains%2C%20the%20Financial%20Times%20reported%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2285c420f3-edb3-4d19-a749-47d6517d18e7%5C%22%3EBuilding%20a%20'digital%20workforce'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20support%20this%20shift%2C%20ProServe%20is%20formalizing%20its%20approach%20to%20deploying%20AI%20agents%2C%20according%20to%20the%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProServe%20outlined%20plans%20to%20establish%20an%20%26quot%3BAgentic%20AI%26quot%3B%20team%20and%20introduce%20an%20%26quot%3BAgent%20Operating%20Model%26quot%3B%20to%20manage%20autonomous%20software%20that%20can%20take%20action%20with%20minimal%20human%20intervention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProServe%20described%20AI%20agents%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bdigital%20workforce%20that%20complements%20human%20teams%26quot%3B%20and%20proposed%20creating%20an%20AI%20Agent%20Service%20and%20Marketplace%20to%20govern%20and%20deploy%20them%2C%20according%20to%20the%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20documents%20from%20June%20projects%20substantial%20productivity%20improvements%2C%20including%20automation%20of%20up%20to%2090%25%20of%20certain%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20positions%20AWS%20as%20a%20leader%20in%20building%20AI%20agents%2C%20and%20managing%20them%20as%20a%20new%20category%20of%20digital%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20June%20document%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2257228301-f643-4b96-b5b7-2033756be9d1%5C%22%3EAmazon%20adapts%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20ProServe%20identified%20early%20that%20%26quot%3Bagentic%20AI%20innovations%26quot%3B%20were%20driving%20a%20shift%20in%20the%20consulting%20industry%20and%20moved%20swiftly%20to%20adapt%20its%20business%20model.%20Customers%20were%20seeking%20outcome-based%2C%20fixed%20pricing%2C%20and%20AWS%20responded%20by%20rolling%20out%20services%20designed%20to%20deliver%20greater%20value%20and%20measurable%20results%2C%20the%20spokesperson%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20AI-powered%20consulting%20model%20accelerates%20customers'%20business%20transformation%2C%20enabling%20them%20to%20innovate%20in%20less%20time%2C%20at%20a%20lower%20cost%2C%20and%20with%20more%20value%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmazon%20shared%20some%20of%20its%20plans%20for%20an%20%26quot%3Bagent-first%20consulting%20approach%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faws.amazon.com%2Fblogs%2Fmachine-learning%2Faccelerate-enterprise-solutions-with-agentic-ai-powered-consulting-introducing-aws-professional-service-agents%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblog%3C%2Fa%3E%20post%20in%20November.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20firms%20are%20following%20suit.%20McKinsey%20CEO%20Bob%20Sternfels%20recently%20said%20the%20consulting%20firm%20added%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmckinsey-ai-agents-ai-adoption-consulting-ey-pwc-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E25%2C000%20AI%20agents%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20its%20staff%20in%20less%20than%202%20years.%20PwC%2C%20EY%2C%20and%20Boston%20Consulting%20Group%20are%20also%20doubling%20down%20on%20deploying%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmckinsey-bcg-pwc-ey-ai-agents-adoption-value-consulting-industry-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20agents%3C%2Fa%3E%20internally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2254c660b0-be8d-4e4e-be8c-ba0a801fab2b%5C%22%3EConsulting%20as%20a%20cloud%20growth%20engine%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20stakes%20are%20high%20for%20Amazon%20Web%20Services%2C%20the%20world's%20largest%20cloud%20provider%2C%20which%20relies%20on%20ProServe%20to%20help%20it%20win%20and%20keep%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20planning%20document%20from%20June%2C%20ProServe's%20consulting%20work%20helped%20AWS%20generate%20roughly%20%2412.5%20billion%20in%20AWS%20revenue%20in%202024.%20The%20unit's%20public-sector%20practice%20alone%20was%20projected%20to%20generate%20more%20than%20%24500%20million%20last%20year%2C%20the%20November%20document%20estimated.%20It%20wants%20to%20help%20AWS%20become%20a%20%24500%20billion%20company%20in%20less%20than%20a%20decade%2C%20the%20June%20document%20stated%2C%20up%20from%20%24129%20billion%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProServe%20has%20already%20seen%20efficiency%20gains%20from%20AI%2C%20according%20to%20the%20documents%20from%20last%20year.%20The%20unit%20was%20on%20pace%20to%20post%20a%20positive%20operating%20margin%20for%20the%20first%20time%20last%20year%20and%20is%20targeting%20a%2020%25%20year-over-year%20increase%20in%20revenue%20per%20employee%20in%202026%20by%20expanding%20its%20use%20of%20AI%20tools.%20It%20also%20expected%20to%20drive%20broader%20AI%20adoption%20among%20AWS%20customers%20without%20materially%20increasing%20headcount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20profitability%20improves%2C%20ProServe%20salespeople%20are%20confronting%20a%20revamped%20pay%20structure.%20Starting%20this%20year%2C%20hundreds%20of%20sales%20employees%20moved%20to%20a%20more%20variable%20compensation%20model%2C%20according%20to%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20shift.%20The%20new%20plan%20cuts%20back%20on%20guaranteed%20stock%20awards%20and%20links%20a%20greater%20portion%20of%20compensation%20to%20performance-based%20incentives%2C%20aligning%20ProServe%20with%20the%20pay%20model%20used%20across%20other%20AWS%20sales%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEnabling%20AWS%20growth%20while%20maintaining%20a%20profitable%20business%20is%20our%20North%20Star%2C%20guiding%20our%20bold%20transformation%20for%202026%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20June%20document%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aekim%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Eekim%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%2C%20Telegram%2C%20or%20WhatsApp%20at%20650-942-3061.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%2C%20a%20nonwork%20WiFi%20network%2C%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ehere's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-aws-cloud-customers-proserve-consulting-fees-ai-automates-work-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772100001000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f38a550f42603b0f8e3c1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-aws-cloud-customers-proserve-consulting-fees-ai-automates-work-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22AWS's%20big%20consulting%20arm%2C%20ProServe%2C%20is%20shifting%20to%20outcome-based%20pricing%2C%20and%20reorganizing%20around%20AI%20agents%20the%20company%20calls%20%26quot%3Bdigital%20employees.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ekim%40businessinsider.com%20(Eugene%20Kim)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-aws-cloud-customers-proserve-consulting-fees-ai-automates-work-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22She%20works%20in%20healthcare%20and%20pays%20%24787%20a%20month%20for%20insurance.%20She%20still%20can't%20afford%20her%20daughter's%20care.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22573%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cassenda%20Nelson%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699734aee1ba468a96ac4eb7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22429%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECassenda%20Nelson%20is%20a%20mother%20of%20four%20in%20southwest%20Georgia.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20Courtesy%20of%20Cassenda%20Nelson%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ECassenda%20Nelson%2C%2047%2C%20struggles%20to%20afford%20care%20for%20her%20daughter's%20complex%20health%20conditions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESteep%20insurance%20premiums%20and%20medical%20debt%20make%20it%20difficult%20to%20afford%20housing%2C%20food%2C%20and%20utilities.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMillions%20of%20Americans%20have%20medical%20debt%2C%20which%20can%20negatively%20affect%20household%20credit%20scores.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ECassenda%20Nelson%20holds%20her%20breath%20when%20the%20phone%20rings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20knows%20that%20it%20could%20be%20a%20hospital%20or%20ambulance%20service%20calling%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcolon-cancer-true-hidden-cost-price-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eunpaid%20bills%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Nelson%20said%20she%20has%20dialed%20911%20several%20times%20in%20recent%20months%20for%20her%2016-year-old%20daughter%2C%20Amunet%2C%20who%20has%20serious%20health%20issues.%20It's%20staggeringly%20expensive%2C%20but%20she%20doesn't%20have%20other%20options%20%E2%80%94%20and%20her%20daughter's%20life%20is%20at%20stake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENelson%20is%20a%20single%20mother%20of%20four%20in%20Camilla%2C%20a%20small%20town%20in%20southwest%20Georgia.%20She%20estimates%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-cervical-cancer-diagnosis-marriage-motherhood-finances-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eher%20medical%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%20exceeds%20%2410%2C000%2C%20though%20she%20said%20the%20total%20is%20likely%20much%20higher.%20The%20ongoing%20cost%20of%20her%20daughter's%20care%20is%20a%20constant%20source%20of%20stress%20and%20has%20affected%20the%20family's%20ability%20to%20afford%20groceries%2C%20rent%2C%20and%20household%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20pay%20what%20I%20can%2C%20what's%20most%20important%2C%26quot%3B%20Nelson%2C%2047%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20any%20other%20help.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20is%20one%20of%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkffhealthnews.org%2Fdiagnosis-debt%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E100%20million%20Americans%20%3C%2Fa%3Esaddled%20with%20medical%20bills%20they%20can't%20pay.%20Healthcare%20debt%20is%20among%20the%20top%20causes%20of%20personal%20bankruptcy%20in%20the%20US%2C%20and%20a%202024%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.healthsystemtracker.org%2Fbrief%2Fthe-burden-of-medical-debt-in-the-united-states%2F%23Share%2520of%2520adults%2520who%2520have%2520medical%2520debt%2C%2520by%2520health%2520status%2520and%2520disability%2520status%2C%25202021%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%20of%20government%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20KFF%20found%20that%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20X%20carry%20the%20most%20debt%20compared%20to%20other%20generations.%20Black%20Americans%20and%20people%20living%20in%20rural%20areas%20are%20at%20the%20highest%20risk%2C%20and%20about%2014%25%20of%20these%20debt%20holders%20owe%20at%20least%20%2410%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FaWmvX%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22230%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ECollection%20agencies%20can't%20legally%20charge%20interest%20on%20medical%20bills%2C%20but%20they%20can%20report%20the%20information%20to%20credit%20bureaus%20if%20the%20balance%20is%20over%20%24500%20for%20at%20least%20one%20year.%20Nelson%20said%20her%20credit%20score%20has%20tumbled%20because%20her%20debt%20is%20above%20this%20threshold.%20The%20cost%20of%20care%20is%20backbreaking%2C%20even%20with%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoung-cancer-work-career-impact-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eemployer-sponsored%20insurance%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Her%20situation%20isn't%20an%20outlier%3A%20Many%20Americans%20with%20medical%20debt%20have%20health%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20I%20can't%20even%20buy%20groceries%2C%26quot%3B%20Nelson%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20make%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20money%2C%20but%20I%20bring%20home%20very%20little%20because%20she%20needs%20to%20have%20the%20best%20insurance.%20When%20I%20was%20on%20other%20insurances%2C%20I%20kept%20getting%20issues%20with%20pre-authorization.%20I%20couldn't%20even%20get%20my%20baby%20insulin.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDo%20you%20have%20a%20healthcare%20story%20to%20share%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3A%2520allisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eallisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20fill%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforms.gle%2FEtPrsD7PaJjLx1pk8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethis%20quick%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2265c32fc4-ed7d-4521-8337-55a1b3c988ff%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHealth%20insurance%20takes%20up%20a%20big%20chunk%20of%20Nelson's%20monthly%20budget%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20past%20five%20years%20have%20been%20a%20whirlwind%20for%20Nelson%20and%20Amunet.%20The%20teenager%20developed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fblood-sugar-levels-track-continuous-glucose-monitor-prevent-diabetes-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etype%202%20diabetes%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202020%2C%20alongside%20a%20seizure%20condition.%20She%20requires%20daily%20access%20to%20insulin%20and%20other%20medications%2C%20full-time%20care%2C%20and%20frequent%20trips%20to%20the%20emergency%20room.%20The%20family%20also%20lives%20in%20a%20rural%20area%2C%20meaning%20they%20sometimes%20travel%20for%20hours%20to%20see%20specialists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENelson%20pays%20%24787%20a%20month%20for%20her%20family's%20health%20insurance.%20She%20works%20as%20a%20community%20healthcare%20worker%20in%20Camilla%2C%20mostly%20focused%20on%20cancer%20screening%20education.%20She%20said%20the%20role%20has%20more%20stable%20coverage%20than%20her%20previous%20employers%20and%20past%20marketplace%20plan%2C%20but%20insurance%20premiums%20are%20a%20big%20part%20of%20her%20monthly%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20Americans%2C%20her%20job%20is%20directly%20tied%20to%20her%20family's%20healthcare%20access.%20Missing%20extra%20days%20or%20hours%20to%20support%20Amunet%20puts%20both%20in%20jeopardy.%20%26quot%3BI%20feel%20heavy%20every%20day%20getting%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Nelson%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20to%20literally%20pray%2C%20'God%2C%20please%20don't%20let%20Amunet%20have%20a%20seizure.%20I%20need%20to%20go%20to%20work%2C%20please.%26quot%3B'%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYears%20of%20paying%20for%20ambulances%2C%20hospital%20stays%2C%20prescriptions%2C%20lab%20tests%2C%20and%20doctor%20co-pays%20have%20bled%20into%20other%20parts%20of%20Nelson's%20life.%20Her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprices-food-coffee-gas-clothes-pets-rent-survey-inflation-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efood%20budget%20has%20shrunk%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20she%20can%20rarely%20afford%20her%20own%20healthcare.%20She%20has%20stopped%20contributing%20to%20her%20son's%20college%20tuition.%20The%20lights%20in%20her%20house%20were%20recently%20shut%20off%20due%20to%20unpaid%20electricity%20bills.%20And%2C%20without%20enough%20money%20to%20hire%20a%20caregiver%20for%20Amunet%2C%20Nelson%20relies%20on%20help%20from%20her%20other%20children%20or%20brings%20her%20daughter%20to%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20debt%20weighs%20on%20her%20too%3A%20Nelson%20said%20she%20and%20her%20family%20recently%20moved%20into%20a%20low-income%20housing%20unit%20because%20she%20could%20no%20longer%20afford%20their%20home.%20And%20the%20hit%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcredit-card-debt-trap-high-interest-rates-retirement-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eher%20credit%20score%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20made%20it%20more%20difficult%20for%20her%20to%20get%20approval%20for%20a%20lease%20or%20an%20auto%20loan%2C%20she%20said.%20Without%20a%20clear%20path%20to%20financial%20stability%2C%20Nelson%20said%20her%20mental%20health%20has%20worsened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20money%2C%20Nelson%20said%20that%20navigating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrue-cost-young-colon-cancer-crisis-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20healthcare%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20especially%20as%20a%20Black%20family%2C%20can%20be%20exhausting.%20There%20are%20hours%20of%20medical%20paperwork%2C%20phone%20calls%20with%20insurance%2C%20meetings%20with%20doctors%2C%20and%20travel%20between%20appointments.%20She%20does%20her%20best%20to%20be%20her%20daughter's%20advocate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20she%20lays%20out%20her%20clothes%20before%20bed%20in%20case%20her%20daughter%20has%20a%20seizure%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night.%20That%20way%2C%20she%20can%20quickly%20change%20before%20the%20ambulance%20arrives.%20%26quot%3BI%20know%20that%20because%20of%20me%20being%20an%20African%20American%20woman%2C%20I%20cannot%20walk%20here%20without%20any%20clothes%20on%20my%20hair%20combed%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20shouldn't%20matter%2C%20but%20I%20have%20to%20present%20my%20best%20self.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENelson%20isn't%20sure%20how%20she%20will%20pay%20her%20next%20set%20of%20bills%2C%20or%20if%20she%20will%20ever%20be%20able%20to%20pay%20down%20her%20medical%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20but%20she%20would%20do%20anything%20for%20Amunet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20give%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20get%20up%20every%20morning%20and%20I%20pray.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-mom-health-insurance-medical-debt-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772099521000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6997353aa645d118818997b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-mom-health-insurance-medical-debt-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cassenda%20Nelson%2C%2047%2C%20is%20overwhelmed%20by%20insurance%20costs%20and%20medical%20debt%20due%20to%20her%20daughter's%20health%20condition.%20She's%20worried%20about%20paying%20bills.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22allisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%20(Allie%20Kelly)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-mom-health-insurance-medical-debt-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Catherine%20Deneuve%20Co-Authors%20%E2%80%98Marilyn%20Ch%C3%A9rie%2C%E2%80%99%20Timed%20to%20Marilyn%20Monroe%E2%80%99s%20100th%20Birthday%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772099387000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236668484%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Catherine%20Deneuve%20has%20co-authored%20a%20book%20dedicated%20to%20the%20late%20icon%2C%20%E2%80%9CMarilyn%20ch%C3%A9rie%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20will%20come%20out%20in%20May%20to%20mark%20the%20centenary%20of%20her%20birth.%20In%20the%20book%2C%20which%20she%20wrote%20with%20collector%20S%C3%A9bastien%20Cauchon%2C%20Deneuve%20delivers%20a%20personal%20look%20at%20photographs%20of%20Monroe%2C%20including%20set%20photos%2C%20costume%20fittings%2C%20portraits%20by%20leading%20photographers%2C%20press%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22auth