view%20process%20now%20includes%20many%20questions%20about%20scenario%20testing.%3Cp%3EJohner%20Images%2FGetty%20Images%2FJohner%20RF%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGoogle%20executive%20Yasmeen%20Ahmad%20said%20she%20is%20looking%20to%20hire%20engineers%20with%20fresh%20ideas.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EShe%20said%20she%20has%20two%20methods%20of%20evaluating%20a%20candidate's%20creativity%20during%20a%20job%20interview.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAhmad%20said%20she%20looks%20for%20%26quot%3Bearly%20adopters%26quot%3B%20and%20those%20who%20can%20use%20AI%20to%20reimagine%20industries.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20executive%20Yasmeen%20Ahmad%20is%20looking%20for%20something%20specific%20when%20hiring%20engineers%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20not%20just%20technical%20know-how.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAhmad%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20typical%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-study-software-engineering-changing-ai-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esoftware%20engineering%20interview%20used%20to%20focus%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20detailed%20coding%20tests%20and%20test%20suites.%20Now%2C%20as%20she%20hires%20for%20a%20forward-deployed%20engineering%20team%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-boosting-hiring-entry-level-engineers-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewill%20work%20with%20customers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20said%20she's%20prioritizing%20people%20with%20fresh%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20strongest%20candidates%20are%20%26quot%3Bable%20to%20think%20outside%20the%20box%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-cloud-exec-how-interns-can-stand-out-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAhmad%2C%20director%20of%20Google%20Cloud's%20data%20cloud%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20able%20to%20think%20outside%20the%20frame%20of%20how%20we%20would%20have%20normally%20described%20a%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20executive%20added%20that%20candidates%20who%20take%20a%20traditional%20approach%20to%20engineering%20aren't%20performing%20as%20well%20in%20her%20team's%20interviews.%20The%20ideal%20candidate%20nowadays%2C%20she%20said%2C%20can%20demonstrate%20creative%20problem-solving%20by%20using%20AI%20to%20reimagine%20traditional%20processes.%20She%20said%20she%20evaluates%20that%20type%20of%20thinking%20in%20two%20ways%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229301862e-2e86-41e1-9ca5-2b66d672b55a%5C%22%3E1.%20Constant%20experimentation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAhmad%20said%20she%20looks%20for%20candidates%20who%20are%20constantly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgooglers-share-transition-to-ai-roles-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Btinkering%26quot%3B%20with%20new%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20gives%20her%20an%20immediate%20signal%20that%20they're%20creative%20thinkers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20interviewing%20them%2C%20they're%20naturally%20immediately%20talking%20about%2C%20'oh%2C%20last%20week%20I%20had%20tried%20AI%20in%20this%20context%2C%20and%20this%20is%20how%20it%20made%20me%20better%20at%20doing%20my%20job%20in%20this%20way%2C'%26quot%3B%20Ahmad%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20candidates%20aren't%20trying%20new%20tools%20because%20their%20boss%20told%20them%20to%20or%20because%20it's%20the%20new%20cool%20thing%20to%20try%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eshe%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20the%20early%20adopters%2C%26quot%3B%20Ahmad%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flinkedin-vp-shares-how-entry-level-engineers-can-stand-out-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETech%20executives%20have%20told%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20side%20projects%20are%20becoming%20increasingly%20common%20for%20candidates%20to%20demonstrate%20their%20aptitude%20in%20interviews.%20However%2C%20Ahmad%20said%20candidates%20don't%20need%20to%20have%20a%20GitHub%20repository%20of%20projects%20they've%20worked%20on%20in%20their%20spare%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20pet%20side%20projects%2C%20because%20people%20are%20busy%2C%26quot%3B%20Ahmad%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20workers%20can%20experiment%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-companies-employees-prove-productivity-rto-performance-reviews-ai-investments-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eon%20the%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20trying%20out%20new%20ways%20to%20speed%20up%20their%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a33dbde0-324c-42b5-a875-7bfcd844310d%5C%22%3E2.%20Scenario%20testing%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20is%20being%20used%20more%20often%20throughout%20the%20interview%20process%20%E2%80%94%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20illicitly%20by%20job%20seekers%2C%20and%20in%20others%2C%20as%20a%20way%20for%20employers%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-canva-meta-tell-some-job-candidates-ok-use-ai-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etest%20candidates'%20AI%20capabilities%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20these%20tools%20reshape%20hiring%2C%20Ahmad%20said%20scenario-based%20testing%20has%20become%20central%20component%20to%20the%20interview%20process%2C%20giving%20hiring%20managers%20a%20better%20way%20to%20assess%20creativity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAhmad%20said%20she'll%20ask%20candidates%20how%20they%20would%20approach%20a%20scenario%20involving%20AI%20tools%20in%20an%20industry%20where%20they%20have%20no%20domain%20knowledge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20if%20the%20example%20related%20to%20healthcare%2C%20a%20traditional%20candidate%20might%20say%20that%20they%20would%20take%20all%20the%20patients'%20unstructured%20PDFs%2C%20feed%20them%20into%20a%20single%20LLM%20prompt%2C%20and%20ask%20it%20to%20generate%20a%20summary%20for%20the%20doctor.%20That%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bmassive%20liability%2C%26quot%3B%20Ahmad%20said%2C%20because%20in%20that%20scenario%20the%20candidate%20assumes%20AI%20can%20inherently%20understand%20the%20timeline%20of%20events%20or%20clinical%20context%20of%20an%20image%20by%20looking%20at%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAhmad%20said%20she's%20looking%20for%20a%20candidate%20who%20can%20%26quot%3Bfind%20solutions%20in%20a%20way%20that%20breaks%20the%20chains%20of%20how%20that%20workflow%20process%20has%20traditionally%20gone.%26quot%3B%20So%20someone%20might%20suggest%20building%20the%20semantic%20context%20for%20the%20imaging%20data%20before%20the%20model%20sees%20it.%20Next%2C%20they%20would%20build%20a%20specific%20framework%20to%20ensure%20the%20agent%20is%20operating%20in%20the%20right%20time%20frame%20of%20data.%20Then%2C%20they%20would%20recommend%20designing%20a%20multi-step%20process%20that%20includes%20a%20continuous%20evaluation%20loop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20aren't%20just%20hiring%20people%20to%20write%20prompts%2C%26quot%3B%20Ahmad%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20hiring%20people%20who%20can%20foresee%20how%20a%20model%20might%20silently%20fail%20in%20a%20high-stakes%20environment%2C%20and%20who%20know%20how%20to%20build%20the%20automated%20evaluation%20loops%20to%20catch%20it%20before%20it%20does.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20asking%20these%20sorts%20of%20questions%20to%20vet%20creativity%20is%20especially%20useful%20as%20AI%20transforms%20the%20software%20engineering%20industry%20by%20automating%20core%20parts%20of%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20seeing%20the%20human%20role%20is%20evolving%20to%20more%20of%20an%20orchestrated%20role%2C%26quot%3B%20Ahmad%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%20rather%20than%20having%20to%20write%20all%20of%20the%20detailed%20code%2C%20it's%20'how%20do%20I%20actually%20express%20my%20intent%20to%20a%20multi-agent%20system%20now%20and%20have%20that%20multi-agent%20system%20execute%20on%20that%20intent%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%2F%2Fembed.typeform.com%2Fnext%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20data-tf-live%3D%5C%2201K0FDNEGB0EC39EGFYGJYGQ07%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-cloud-exec-how-to-show-creativity-in-interviews-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772098621000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699dffdadf1f09368aaaac90%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-cloud-exec-how-to-show-creativity-in-interviews-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Google%20Cloud%20executive%20Yasmeen%20Ahmad%20says%20she%20looks%20for%20candidates%20who%20show%20creative%20problem-solving%20in%20technical%20interviews.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-cloud-exec-how-to-show-creativity-in-interviews-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Kerala%20HC%20stays%20release%20of%20'The%20Kerala%20Story%202'%2C%20says%20censors%20didn't%20'apply%20mind'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772098598000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-128809099%2Cimgsize-1019664.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fkerala-hc-stays-the-kerala-story-2-for-15-days-a-day-before-scheduled-release%2Farticleshow%2F128809017.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Kerala%20High%20Court%20has%20issued%20an%20interim%20stay%20on%20the%20release%20of%20'The%20Kerala%20Story%202%3A%20Goes%20Beyond'%2C%20scheduled%20for%20February%2027.%20The%20court%20observed%20a%20prima%20facie%20non-application%20of%20mind%20by%20the%20censor%20board%20in%20granting%20certification.%20This%20decision%20follows%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20film's%20certificate%2C%20citing%20concerns%20about%20its%20portrayal%20of%20religious%20harmony%20in%20Kerala.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20NEWS%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fkerala-hc-stays-the-kerala-story-2-for-15-days-a-day-before-scheduled-release%2Farticleshow%2F128809017.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20job%20market%20is%20in%20a%20'deep%20freeze.'%20One%20industry%20is%20keeping%20it%20from%20sliding%20backward.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228038%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20sign%20that's%20mainly%20red%20says%20%26quot%3Bhelp%20wanted%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Binquire%20within%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f1533e8408f6671803a83%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%226029%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20US%20job%20market%20has%20been%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bdeep%20freeze.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EO2O%20Creative%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20job%20market%20is%20heavily%20leaning%20on%20the%20healthcare%20and%20social%20assistance%20sector.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20sector%20has%20grown%2018%25%20from%20January%202019%20compared%20to%20a%20measly%204%25%20for%20all%20other%20nonfarm%20payrolls.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHealthcare%20and%20social%20assistance%20accounted%20for%20all%20net%20job%20growth%20in%20the%20US%20last%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20industry%20hasn't%20chilled%20just%20yet%20in%20the%20job%20market's%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flow-hire-low-fire-layoffs-employees-stuck-unemployment-job-seekers-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGreat%20Freeze%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20it%20will%20likely%20continue%20to%20persevere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20ongoing%20low-hire%2C%20low-fire%20job%20market%2C%20job%20seekers%20can%20still%20find%20opportunities%20in%20the%20private%20healthcare%20and%20social%20assistance%20sector%2C%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20data%20showed.%20Employment%20in%20this%20sector%20has%20grown%2018%25%20from%20January%202019%2C%20compared%20to%204%25%20for%20all%20other%20nonfarm%20payrolls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FtOTFA%2F2%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Healthcare%20and%20nonfarm%20payrolls%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22528%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20divide%20has%20gotten%20even%20more%20stark%20in%20the%20last%20year.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-report-january-data-live-updates-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elatest%20jobs%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20that%20the%20US%20added%20only%20181%2C000%20jobs%20in%202025%3B%20healthcare%20and%20social%20assistance%20added%20693%2C200%20jobs%20over%20the%20year.%20That%20means%20the%20job%20market%20would%20have%20lost%20about%20half%20a%20million%20jobs%20without%20this%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20healthcare%20industry%20was%20such%20an%20important%20driver%20of%20jobs%20growth%20in%202025%20that%20we%20are%20going%20to%20want%20to%20watch%20it%20closely%20in%202026%20for%20any%20signs%20of%20a%20slowdown%2C%26quot%3B%20Daniel%20Zhao%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20at%20Glassdoor%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAs%20jobs%20growth%20in%20the%20labor%20market%20becomes%20more%20narrow%2C%20we%20are%20relying%20increasingly%20on%20healthcare%20to%20keep%20us%20in%20the%20green.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpportunities%20for%20doctors%2C%20nurses%2C%20and%20similar%20professionals%20are%20less%20vulnerable%20to%20the%20uncertainty%20that's%20been%20prevalent%20in%20the%20job%20market.%20Job-market%20experts%20said%20healthcare%20and%20social%20assistance%20work%20will%20remain%20important%20as%20the%20population%20ages%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-i-learnt-from-60-people-about-retiring-early-fire-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople%20retire%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHealthcare%20is%20definitely%20a%20job-producing%20engine%20that%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20Christian%20Gomez%2C%20a%20vice%20president%20at%20ADP%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3EDid%20you%20make%20a%20career%20pivot%20into%20healthcare%2C%20or%20are%20you%20unemployed%20and%20willing%20to%20share%20what%20your%20job%20search%20has%20been%20like%3F%20Reach%20out%20to%20this%20reporter%20to%20share%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Amhoff%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emhoff%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Faside%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20broader%20job%20market%20continues%20to%20be%20defined%20by%20job%20seekers%20struggling%20to%20get%20off%20the%20sidelines%20and%20seeking%20new%20career%20options.%20Gregory%20Daco%2C%20the%20chief%20economist%20at%20EY%2C%20said%20the%20job%20market%20is%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bdeep%20freeze%2C%26quot%3B%20indicated%20by%20a%20few%20data%20points%20taken%20together%3A%20recent%20hires%20rates%20are%20comparable%20to%20low%20rates%20in%202013%20when%20the%20job%20market%20was%20still%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcant-find-job-labor-market-hiring-great-recession-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecovering%20from%20the%20Great%20Recession%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20quit%20rates%20have%20tumbled%20since%20the%20post-pandemic%20%26quot%3BGreat%20Resignation%26quot%3B%20when%20workers%20felt%20confident%20they'd%20be%20able%20to%20find%20a%20new%20gig%2C%20and%20openings%20are%20low%20compared%20to%20demand%20from%20job%20seekers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22478dad57-aafe-4eac-ac44-0605ca9ff5a2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EGetting%20into%20healthcare%20and%20social%20assistance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELaura%20Ullrich%2C%20the%20director%20of%20economic%20research%20in%20North%20America%20at%20the%20Indeed%20Hiring%20Lab%2C%20said%20Indeed%20data%20shows%20many%20of%20the%20job%20postings%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-paying-growing-demand-jobs-healthcare-nurse-therapist-job-security-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealthcare%20sector%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20traditional%20medical%20roles%2C%20such%20as%20technicians%2C%20physicians%2C%20and%20dentists%2C%20rather%20than%20software%20engineers%20and%20accountants%2C%20although%20there%20are%20also%20openings%20for%20non-clinical%20roles%20in%20this%20particular%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20difficult%20for%20people%20just%20to%20switch%20from%20being%20an%20employee%20in%20financial%20activities%2C%20for%20example%2C%20and%20then%20shift%20to%20healthcare%2C%26quot%3B%20Ullrich%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20doesn't%20mean%20you%20need%20to%20go%20to%20medical%20school%20to%20get%20into%20the%20industry.%20Gomez%2C%20who%20connects%20with%20some%20big%20hospitals%2C%20said%20as%20more%20people%20depend%20on%20health%20services%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat%20doesn't%20just%20mean%20that%20clinical%20roles%20are%20the%20ones%20that%20will%20be%20creating%20opportunities%20for%20people%20entering%20the%20job%20market.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20there%20are%20tech%2C%20caregiving%2C%20human%20resources%2C%20and%20finance%20opportunities%20already%20in%20demand%20within%20healthcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBLS%20data%20from%20May%202024%20shows%20that%20the%20healthcare%20and%20social%20assistance%20sector%20employs%20plenty%20of%20secretaries%20and%20administrative%20assistants%2C%20as%20well%20as%20receptionists%20and%20information%20clerks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fdp1oh%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Healthcare%20and%20social%20assistance%20employment%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22995%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthcare-social-assistance-opportunities-job-market-deep-freeze-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772098561000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f1533e8408f6671803a83%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthcare-social-assistance-opportunities-job-market-deep-freeze-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20US%20barely%20added%20any%20jobs%20last%20year%2C%20but%20one%20sector%20is%20still%20hiring%20at%20a%20fast%20clip.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Madison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthcare-social-assistance-opportunities-job-market-deep-freeze-2026-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20relief%20for%20the%2040%20million%20Americans%20without%20a%20retirement%20account%20could%20work%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226861%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Trump%20giving%20his%20State%20of%20the%20Union%20speech.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f5c2fe8408f6671804418%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224574%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20unveiled%20a%20new%20retirement%20saving%20policy%20in%20his%202026%20State%20of%20the%20Union%20speech.%3Cp%3EPool%20photo%20by%20Kenny%20Holston%2FThe%20New%20York%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EPresident%20Trump%20hopes%20to%20match%20retirement%20savings%20for%20private-sector%20employees%20without%20company%20plans.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20plan%20would%20expand%20a%20Biden-era%20law%20that%20helps%20fund%20retirement%20for%20low-income%20workers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEconomists%20had%20mixed%20reviews%20of%20the%20proposal.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20line%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-state-of-union-speech-economy-taxes-inflation-fed-housing-2026-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETrump's%20State%20of%20the%20Union%3C%2Fa%3E%20address%20could%20be%20good%20news%20for%20hopeful%20retirees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20proposed%20an%20expansion%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployer-sponsored-retirement-plans-social-security-savings-boomers-aarp-report-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eretirement%20savings%20%3C%2Fa%3Efor%20Americans%20without%20401(k)s%20and%20other%20employer-provided%20retirement%20plans%20during%20his%20Tuesday%20speech.%20He%20said%20the%20federal%20government%20will%20soon%20match%20individual%20savings%20up%20to%20%241%2C000%20a%20year.%20Over%2040%20million%20Americans%20who%20work%20full-time%20don't%20have%20a%20retirement%20plan%2C%20and%20nearly%2049%20million%20don't%20have%20employer%20matching%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Economic%20Innovation%20Group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNext%20year%2C%20my%20administration%20will%20give%20these%20often%20forgotten%20American%20workers%2C%20great%20people%2C%20the%20people%20that%20built%20our%20country%2C%20access%20to%20the%20same%20type%20of%20retirement%20plan%20offered%20to%20every%20federal%20worker%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20president%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20match%20your%20contribution%20with%20up%20to%20%241%2C000%20each%20year%2C%20as%20we%20ensure%20that%20all%20Americans%20can%20profit%20from%20a%20rising%20stock%20market.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20plan%20comes%20to%20fruition%2C%20it%20could%20help%20mitigate%20a%20financial%20reality%20for%20both%20blue-%20and%20white-collar%20workers%3A%20the%20safety%20net%20often%20isn't%20enough%20to%20support%20aging%20Americans.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20recently%20interviewed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretirement-regrets-saving-investing-loneliness-parenting-older-americans-survey-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehundreds%20of%20older%20adults%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20live%20on%20Social%20Security.%20Many%20told%20us%20that%20they%20struggle%20to%20afford%20housing%2C%20groceries%2C%20and%20healthcare%20without%20adequate%20retirement%20savings%2C%20and%20others%20remain%20in%20the%20workforce%20to%20make%20ends%20meet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20to%20know%20about%20the%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22aa7b2c93-2167-4e4c-8fe2-13166b3cbef2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20it%20will%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETrump's%20retirement-matching%20policy%20is%20intended%20for%20private-sector%20workers%20who%20don't%20qualify%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faging-workforce-retirement-google-microsoft-walmart-starbucks-corporate-america-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eemployer-sponsored%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20White%20House%20official%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20government-matched%20savings%20account%20will%20operate%20similarly%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fpersonal-loans%2Fthrift-savings-plan-loan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20Thrift%20Savings%20Program%3C%2Fa%3E%20available%20to%20federal%20workers%2C%20offering%20index-based%20investment%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20official%20said%20that%20these%20savings%20accounts%20will%20be%20available%20even%20as%20workers%20change%20jobs%2C%20like%20a%20typical%20401(k)%2C%20and%20private%20philanthropists%20will%20be%20able%20to%20contribute%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20White%20House's%20estimate%2C%20the%20savings-match%20policy%20will%20immediately%20make%2056%20million%20previously%20uncovered%20workers%20eligible%20to%20save%20through%20a%20low-fee%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feig.org%2Fwhos-left-out-of-americas-retirement-savings-system%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EForty-two%20percent%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20full-time%20Americans%20don't%20have%20access%20to%20retirement%20plans%20at%20all%2C%20and%20half%20don't%20have%20an%20employer-match%20option%20through%20their%20job%2C%20EIG%20researchers%20found.%20The%20National%20Institute%20of%20Retirement%20Security%20also%20reported%20that%20the%20median%20American%20worker%20has%20just%20%24955%20saved%20for%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDozens%20of%20the%20nearly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F80-over-80-watch-video-read-all-stories-2025%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E200%20workers%2080%20and%20older%3C%2Fa%3E%20whom%20Business%20Insider%20interviewed%20last%20year%20said%20that%20they%20never%20worked%20jobs%20that%20set%20them%20up%20with%20a%20401(k)%20or%20retirement%20plan.%20Many%20were%20on%20their%20own%20in%20preparing%20for%20retirement%2C%20and%20without%20proper%20financial%20education%2C%20some%20said%20they%20could%20never%20get%20ahead%20and%20were%20reliant%20on%20Social%20Security%20and%20work%20income%20to%20get%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-will-social-security-benefits-run-out-retirement-crisis-boomers-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ESocial%20Security's%20trust%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20set%20to%20dry%20out%20in%20under%20a%20decade%2C%20which%20could%20result%20in%20cuts%20to%20monthly%20checks%20of%20over%2020%25.%20Though%20Trump%20mentioned%20protecting%20Social%20Security%20in%20his%20address%2C%20he%20offered%20no%20plan%20to%20address%20the%20funding%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20after%20the%20State%20of%20the%20Union%20address%2C%20Treasury%20Secretary%20Scott%20Bessent%20told%20NBC%20News%20that%20the%20plan%20%26quot%3Bis%20going%20to%20be%20a%20very%20big%20part%20of%20working%20Americans'%20retirement%20program%20because%20there%20is%20a%20tremendous%20amount%20of%20financial%20insecurity.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%20that%2038%25%20of%20Americans%20have%20no%20exposure%20to%20the%20equity%20market%2C%20and%20this%20plan%2C%20coupled%20with%20Trump%20Accounts%20for%20children%2C%20could%20expand%20access.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20has%20not%20outlined%20a%20timeline%20for%20the%20program's%20rollout%20but%20said%20Trump%20will%20share%20updated%20details%20soon.%20The%20administration%20hasn't%20specified%20whether%20the%20program%20will%20have%20any%20age%2C%20income%2C%20or%20working-hour%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.finance.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2FSecure%25202.0_Section%2520by%2520Section%2520Summary%252012-19-22%2520FINAL.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2022%20SECURE%202.0%20law%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20similar%20federal%20retirement%20matching%20available%20to%20some%20low-income%20Americans%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20White%20House%20hopes%20to%20build%20on%20this%20existing%20framework.%20But%20enacting%20the%20policy%20at%20a%20wider%20scale%20would%20likely%20need%20Congressional%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2205ba8417-42dd-405e-a513-ce445debfc1e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20economists%20are%20saying%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20economists%20praised%20the%20plan%20as%20a%20step%20in%20the%20right%20direction%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwealth-inequality-so-bad-will-take-230-years-end-poverty-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eclosing%20the%20wealth%20gap%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Teresa%20Ghilarducci%2C%20a%20labor%20economist%20at%20The%20New%20School%20who%20studies%20retirement%20security%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Trump's%20plan%20could%20help%20close%20the%20retirement%20coverage%20gap%20for%20many%20lower-income%20workers%20if%20it's%20implemented%20effectively.%20She%20described%20the%20plan%20as%20%26quot%3Bincremental%20but%20nontrivial.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20Traditional%20and%20Roth%20IRAs%20are%20available%20to%20those%20without%20employer%20coverage%2C%20these%20accounts%20can%20feel%20intimidating%20for%20individuals%20who%20are%20less%20confident%20in%20managing%20their%20finances.%20A%20government-administered%20plan%20established%20through%20an%20election%20on%20an%20annual%20tax%20return%20could%20lower%20the%20barrier%20to%20entry%20and%20provide%20a%20visible%20incentive%20to%20contribute%20through%20a%20matching%20benefit%2C%26quot%3B%20Bankrate%20financial%20analyst%20Stephen%20Kates%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20adding%20that%20many%20questions%20remain%20about%20eligibility%20rules%20and%20how%20assets%20will%20be%20handled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration%20did%20not%20fully%20address%20how%20the%20%241%2C000%20match%20would%20be%20funded.%20Romina%20Boccia%2C%20director%20of%20budget%20and%20entitlement%20policy%20at%20the%20Cato%20Institute%2C%20said%20that%20the%20administration%20lacks%20the%20fiscal%20authority%20to%20carry%20this%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoccia%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20real%20problem%20isn't%20a%20shortage%20of%20government-sponsored%20savings%20vehicles.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20low-income%20and%20younger%20earners%20don't%20participate%20in%20401(k)s%20because%20it%20often%20doesn't%20make%20economic%20sense%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Boccia%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BThey%20face%20pressing%20short-term%20needs%20%E2%80%94%20housing%2C%20emergencies%2C%20education%2C%20starting%20a%20family%20%E2%80%94%20and%20locking%20up%20savings%20until%20age%2059%C2%BD%20with%20penalties%20for%20early%20access%20can%20leave%20them%20worse%20off.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGhilarducci%20called%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomers-regret-financing-retirement-social-security-401k-investing-stocks-cancer-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eweakened%20pensions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20static%20wages%2C%20and%20tax%20subsidies%20that%20disproportionately%20benefit%20higher-income%20earners%20as%20other%20issues%20standing%20in%20the%20way%20of%20many%20workers%20retiring.%20Additionally%2C%20she%20wrote%20in%20a%20note%20after%20the%20State%20of%20the%20Union%20that%20the%20plan%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20substantially%20change%20the%20regressivity%20of%20existing%20retirement%20tax%20expenditures%2C%20nor%20does%20it%20change%20the%20voluntary%20architecture%20that%20has%20produced%20large%20wealth%20gaps.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAccess%20alone%20does%20not%20ensure%20adequacy%20or%20equity%2C%20and%20the%20accounts%20must%20not%20be%20used%20to%20reduce%20eligibility%20for%20relief%20programs%20or%20take%20away%20from%20Medicare%2C%26quot%3B%20Ghilarducci%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BProgressives%20could%20use%20this%20as%20an%20opening%20to%20lift%20up%20the%20need%20for%20Social%20Security%20funding%20and%20a%20universal%20supplement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-hopes-to-boost-retirement-savings-for-private-sector-workers-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1772098081000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F699f5c4a50f42603b0f8e883%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-hopes-to-boost-retirement-savings-for-private-sector-workers-2026-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22President%20Donald%20Trump%20announced%20a%20federal%20savings%20match%20plan%20for%20private-sector%20workers%20during%20his%202026%20State%20of%20the%20Union%20speech.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22allisonkelly%40businessinsider.com%20(Allie%20Kelly%2CNoah%20Sheidlower)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrum