0rules.%20No%20one%20will%20bat%20an%20eye%20at%20what%20you%20order%20%E2%80%94%20or%20what%20time.%20It's%20one%20of%20the%20last%20true%20democratic%20spaces%20left%2C%20a%20place%20that%20holds%20the%20full%20range%20of%20human%20emotions%2C%20from%20anxiety%20to%20excitement%20to%20despair.%20You%20bond%20with%20a%20stranger%20over%20a%20drink%2C%20swap%20stories%2C%20commiserate%20about%20a%20flight%20delay%2C%20and%20then%20disappear%20to%20separate%20gates%2C%20never%20to%20cross%20paths%20again.%20In%20a%20world%20where%20third%20spaces%20are%20dying%2C%20and%20consumers%20are%20being%20segregated%20between%20haves%20and%20have-nots%20at%20every%20turn%2C%20the%20airport%20bar%20has%20quietly%20endured.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20airport%20bar%20is%20not-so-quietly%20under%20siege.%20Airport%20concessions%20took%20a%20hit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fair-traffic-during-coronavirus-pandemic-changes-effects-around-the-world-2020-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eduring%20the%20pandemic%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20while%20they%20benefited%20from%20the%20subsequent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgenz-millennials-summer-travel-debt-remote-work-blame-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erevenge%20travel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20rebound%20has%20stalled.%20Financially%20strained%20consumers%20are%20pinching%20pennies%2C%20including%20at%20airport%20vendors%20known%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-are-airports-so-expensive%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epush%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20there%20is%20the%20bar's%20elitist%20counterpoint%3A%20the%20airport%20lounge.%20These%20spaces%20are%20increasingly%20overcrowded%2C%20and%20more%20and%20more%20passengers%20are%20wondering%20whether%20they're%20delivering%20the%20bang%20for%20their%20buck%2C%20but%20they're%20still%20a%20formidable%20competitor%20to%20the%20airport's%20more%20traditional%20food%20and%20drink%20options.%20When%20a%20new%20lounge%20opens%20near%20a%20restaurant%20or%20bar%2C%20the%20established%20businesses%20say%20sales%20often%20drop%2C%20sometimes%20by%20double%20digits.%20They%20also%20say%20they're%20not%20in%20a%20fair%20fight%3A%20airport%20bars%20have%20to%20turn%20a%20profit%20despite%20their%20high%20operational%20costs.%20Lounges%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20are%20largely%20marketing%20tools%20for%20airlines%20and%20banks%20%E2%80%94%20they%20are%20designed%20as%20perks%20to%20sell%20status%20and%20loyalty%20rather%20than%20to%20make%20a%20ton%20of%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou're%20paying%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Bfree%26quot%3B%20stuff%20in%20the%20lounge%20in%20some%20way%2C%20shape%2C%20or%20form%20%E2%80%94%20say%2C%20with%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famex-platinum-credit-card-new-annual-fee-regrets-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24895-a-year%20Amex%20Platinum%20card%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20but%20you%20don't%20%3Cem%3Efeel%20%3C%2Fem%3Eit%20in%20the%20immediate%20way%20you%20do%20a%20%2425%20glass%20of%20wine%20at%20the%20bar.%20Plus%2C%20in%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-new-hours-fees-changing-prices-tiers-customer-caste-system-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincreasingly%20tiered%20consumer%20economy%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20lounge%20seems%20fancy.%20The%20airport%20bar%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20egalitarian%20experiences%20in%20an%20era%20where%20essentially%20nothing%20else%20about%20flying%20is.%20It's%20primed%20for%20a%20comeback%20%E2%80%94%20the%20next%20time%20your%20layover%20goes%20from%20one%20hour%20to%20two%2C%20instead%20of%20spending%2045%20minutes%20in%20line%20for%20the%20lounge%2C%20see%20what's%20up%20at%20the%20terminal%20tavern.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20airport%20is%20an%20unusual%20space%20to%20begin%20with.%20It's%20a%20place%20oriented%20around%20both%20mobility%20and%20immobility%20%E2%80%94%20it%20often%20takes%20as%20much%20time%20to%20get%20to%20your%20flight%20as%20it%20does%20to%20fly%20to%20your%20destination%2C%20if%20not%20more.%20This%20hurry-up-and-wait%20mode%20of%20travel%20creates%20anxiety%20for%20many%20passengers.%20Yes%2C%20you%20can%20sit%20at%20the%20gate%20and%20wait%20patiently%20for%20free%2C%20but%20that's%20not%20particularly%20fun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20an%20opportunity%20for%20airports%2C%20which%20generate%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20retail%20revenue%20each%20year.%20Still%2C%20for%20the%20bars%2C%20restaurants%2C%20and%20retail%20shops%20that%20sign%20up%20to%20cater%20to%20airport%20customers%2C%20operating%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-airports-trick-you-spending-money%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebehind%20security%20is%20expensive%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Businesses%20pay%20high%20rents%2C%20often%20share%20a%20percentage%20of%20their%20sales%20with%20airports%2C%20and%20must%20navigate%20the%20logistics%20of%20getting%20staff%20and%20inventory%20through%20checkpoints.%20All%20of%20this%20gets%20baked%20into%20your%20bar%20tab%20%E2%80%94%20that%20eye-popping%20price%20tag%20on%20a%20pre-flight%20gin%20and%20tonic%20is%20part%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20doing%20business%20in%20a%20captive%2C%20controlled%20environment.%20While%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-airport-beers-audit-otg-management-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eairport%20retailers%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20supposed%20to%20be%20limited%20in%20how%20much%20they%20can%20upcharge%20you%2C%20it%20often%20seems%20like%20the%20limit%20does%20not%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20was%2C%20of%20course%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fphotos-year-apart-show-pandemics-effect-on-air-traffic-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20miserable%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20be%20operating%20on%20the%20far%20side%20of%20TSA%2C%20but%20things%20are%20still%20rough.%20While%20passenger%20volumes%20at%20airports%20have%20bounced%20back%2C%20business%20for%20many%20retailers%20has%20stalled%2C%20says%20Andrew%20Weddig%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20Airport%20Restaurant%20and%20Retail%20Association.%20In%202024%2C%20a%20majority%20of%20ARRA's%20members%20saw%20an%20increase%20in%20same-store%20sales%20from%20the%20year%20before%3B%20in%202025%2C%20a%20majority%20saw%20a%20decrease.%20%26quot%3BTransactions%20and%20sales%20are%20sluggish%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20issue%20is%20affordability%2C%20as%20consumers%20search%20for%20places%20in%20their%20budgets%20to%20save.%20A%20trip%20to%20the%20airport%20bar%20is%20a%20pretty%20easy%20way%20to%20blow%20%2450%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20easy%20to%20avoid.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20got%20a%20general%20decline%20going%20on%20in%20the%20economy%20right%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Weddig%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20bigger%20culprit%20of%20airport%20concessionaires'%20woes%2C%20he%20argues%2C%20is%20the%20lounges.%20Three-quarters%20of%20ARRA's%20members%20with%20lounges%20open%20nearby%20have%20reported%20a%20drop%20in%20sales%2C%20some%20as%20much%20as%2014%25.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20changing%20the%20flow%20of%20passengers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELounges%20are%20often%20installed%20when%20retailers%20are%20midway%20through%20their%20lease%20terms%2C%20instantly%20creating%20new%20competition%20and%20making%20concepts%20that%20may%20have%20made%20sense%20before%20the%20lounge%20obsolete.%20In%20a%20particularly%20nasty%20twist%20of%20fate%2C%20another%20major%20problem%20for%20airport%20businesses%20is%20credit%20card%20swipe%20fees%2C%20which%20card%20issuers%20use%20to%20pay%20for%20the%20lounges%20they're%20now%20losing%20business%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ELounges%20are%20changing%20both%20the%20economics%20and%20culture%20of%20airports.%20They%20originated%20in%20the%20late%201930s%20and%201940s%20as%20literal%20private%20clubs%2C%20explains%20Kevin%20James%2C%20a%20history%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Guelph%20who%20has%20studied%20their%20development.%20After%20World%20War%20II%2C%20their%20super-restricted%20status%20eroded%2C%20and%20by%20the%201970s%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20exclusive%2C%20luxurious%20club%20idea%20was%20more%20or%20less%20dead%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20Sure%2C%20there%20are%20some%20ultra-luxurious%20spaces%20somewhere%20in%20some%20airports%2C%20but%20in%20general%2C%20%26quot%3Btravel%20has%20become%20more%20democratic%2C%20and%20so%20has%20the%20airport%20lounge.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20%26quot%3Bdemocratic%26quot%3B%20doesn't%20mean%20open%20to%20everyone%20all%20at%20once.%20Access%20is%20organized%20by%20credit%20card%2C%20loyalty%20status%2C%20and%20day%20pass.%20The%20space%20is%20no%20longer%20reserved%20for%20a%20tiny%20elite%20class%2C%20but%20it%20is%20still%20gated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20more%20people%20have%20gained%20lounge%20access%2C%20what's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisappointing-photos-exclusive-airport-lounges-food-lines-reality-vs-expectation-2018-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebehind%20the%20gate%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20not%20so%20enticing%20anymore%2C%20or%20so%20friction-free.%20The%20areas%20are%20packed.%20Passengers%20often%20find%20themselves%20waiting%20in%20long%20lines%20just%20to%20grab%20a%20few%20free%20bites%20at%20the%20subpar%20buffet.%20Or%2C%20they%20present%20themselves%20at%20the%20lounge%20counter%2C%20only%20to%20be%20denied%20entry%20because%20their%20credit%20card%20or%20ticket%20no%20longer%20grants%20the%20same%20access%20it%20did%20after%20the%20airline%20or%20bank%20changed%20the%20terms.%20Lounges%20are%20still%20growing%20%E2%80%94%20a%20majority%20of%20frequent%20flyers%20visit%20them%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchandmarkets.com%2Freport%2Fairport-lounges%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20lounge%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20expected%20to%20reach%20nearly%20%2410%20billion%20in%20annual%20revenue%20by%202029%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they're%20not%20all%20they're%20cracked%20up%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20word%20lounge%20telegraphs%20something%20that%20almost%20invariably%20disappoints%20the%20lounge%20goer%2C%26quot%3B%20James%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20kind%20of%20a%20glorified%20gate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20lounges%20are%20a%20net%20negative%20for%20airport%20bars%2C%20the%20overcrowding%20situation%20may%20have%20some%20silver%20lining.%20Lounges%20drive%20higher-end%20consumers%20to%20certain%20airports%20and%20terminals%2C%20says%20Blaise%20Waguespack%2C%20a%20marketing%20professor%20at%20Embry-Riddle%20Aeronautical%20University.%20If%20those%20people%20find%20themselves%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20they%20can't%20get%20into%20the%20lounge%2C%20a%20nearby%20restaurant%20or%20bar%20may%20well%20become%20Plan%20B.%20%26quot%3BVery%20few%20of%20us%20say%2C%20'Oh%2C%20wait%2C%20there's%20a%20line%20here%2C%20I'm%20just%20going%20to%20go%20sit%20outside%20the%20door%20and%20wait%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20unlike%20the%20lounge%2C%20the%20airport%20bar%20is%20never%20going%20to%20turn%20you%20away.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20almost%20a%20humiliating%20experience%20for%20people%20because%20they%20walk%20up%20to%20the%20concierge%20and%20they%20flash%20their%20card%20and%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20they%20discover%20that's%20not%20enough%20to%20get%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20James%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20lounge%20culture%2C%20American%20culture%20is%20shifting%20around%20the%20airport%20bar%20as%20well.%20Young%20people%20are%20drinking%20less%2C%20so%20a%20stop%20for%20a%20beer%20to%20calm%20some%20pre-flight%20jitters%20may%20not%20be%20on%20the%20agenda.%20Others%20are%20eschewing%20an%20airport%20cocktail%20because%20in%20the%20age%20of%20social%20media%20and%20constant%20surveillance%2C%20if%20only%20by%20strangers%20with%20a%20cellphone%2C%20nothing%20you%20do%20is%20truly%20anonymous%20anymore.%20Have%20one%20too%20many%20or%20let%20something%20slip%20that%20would%20best%20remain%20private%2C%20and%20you%20risk%20becoming%20an%20unwitting%20internet%20star.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMaybe%20the%20old%20days%2C%20where%20somebody%20might've%20sat%20there%20on%20a%20bar%20stool%20and%20drank%20their%20misery%20away%2C%20that%20behavior%20just%20won't%20fly%20anymore%2C%20if%20you%20will%2C%26quot%3B%20Waguespack%20says.%20%26quot%3BEverybody's%20got%20a%20camera%20these%20days.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20airport%20bar%20is%20still%20open%20to%20everyone%2C%20but%20the%20freedom%20it%20offers%20is%20narrower.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20this%20is%20to%20romanticize%20the%20airport%20bar.%20It's%20expensive.%20It's%20often%20crowded.%20The%20food%20and%20drinks%20can%20be%20mediocre.%20And%20there's%20a%20difference%20between%20having%20a%20pre-flight%20prosecco%20and%20getting%20so%20drunk%20you're%20denied%20boarding%20%E2%80%94%20a%20problem%20airlines%20wrestled%20with%20after%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%2C%20however%2C%20something%20compellingly%20equalizing%20about%20the%20airport%20bar%2C%20especially%20when%20so%20much%20of%20the%20consumer%20economy%20has%20been%20stratified%20into%20tiers.%20The%20other%20passengers%20at%20the%20bar%20may%20be%20flying%20a%20higher%20class%20than%20you%2C%20or%20at%20least%20not%20stuck%20in%20the%20inferno%20that%20is%20basic%20economy%2C%20but%20we're%20all%20a%20bit%20helpless%20in%20the%20face%20of%20weather%2C%20delays%2C%20and%20whatever%20other%20unwelcome%20adventure%20our%20flight%20travels%20often%20have%20in%20store.%20And%20hey%2C%20maybe%20one%20of%20the%20rich%20people%20will%20feel%20bad%20for%20you%20and%20pick%20up%20your%20tab.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOutside%20the%20airport%2C%20consumers%20are%20constantly%20being%20nudged%20toward%20various%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsumer-loyalty-dead-airline-miles-internet-company-car-insurance-prices-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloyalty%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20paid%20perks%20that%20offer%20a%20slight%20edge.%20You%20can%20pay%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdisney-genie-plus-skip-lines-worth-it-for-family-disneyland-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eskip%20the%20line%20at%20Disney%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20shop%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcostco-executive-member-hours-early-shopping-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Especial%20hours%20at%20Costco%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20get%20your%20Lyft%20to%20show%20up%20a%20few%20minutes%20earlier.%20Corporations%20unbundle%20services%20and%20throw%20up%20walls%20as%20a%20way%20to%20extract%20as%20much%20money%20as%20possible%20from%20customers%2C%20recognizing%20that%20if%20you%20create%20a%20system%20of%20winners%20and%20losers%2C%20some%20number%20of%20people%20are%20willing%20to%20pay%20to%20be%20a%20winner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20airport%20bar%20is%20one%20of%20the%20increasingly%20limited%20spaces%20in%20life%20that%20work%20against%20that.%20Sitting%20in%20front%20of%20the%20bartender%2C%20hoping%20no%20one%20will%20judge%20you%20for%20ordering%20that%207%20am%20screwdriver%20after%20awkwardly%20climbing%20onto%20the%20barstool%20and%20nearly%20tripping%20over%20your%20luggage%20in%20the%20process%2C%20we%20are%20all%20equal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fairport-lounge-vs-bar-travel-flying-2026-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3